Thank you very much (Sorry about the block wall of text lol)

title: Design the logo for a rebellious new school (and education paradigm)
description: The Collins Institute for Gifted Youth (CollinsInstitute.org)—or “The Collins Institute” more simply—is new educational system aimed at being the primary competitor to Elon Musk's school and the most prestigious boarding schools (like Andover and Exeter).
other_notes:
[UPDATE]
When compared with the options that have been presented so far, we like our placeholder logo better (the only reason we are looking for something else is it is already the logo for our sexuality book). The primary reasons are twofold:
1. It is much simpler / more minimalist
2. It does not look like a community college / technical school logo.
We want to avoid looking like a community college or a “normal” online school. We should instead be drifting more towards something you would see as a logo for a Google product but even simpler (e.g. one of the logos from our book series).
Ideally the school will look like an iteration in the logo series for our books. (here is a link to the book series https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B…ype=ebooks
We have also attached some files to give you an idea of the level o simplicity we are looking for as well as an .ai file for the sexuality book so you can take the logo from that.
[ORIGINAL COMMENTS]
We want the logo to symbolize:
Prestige / Power / Superiority
Independence / Freedom / Rebellion
Themes:
A destruction of the factory education model
A gear or gears (we will heavily preference designs using gears, as this is funded by the Pragmatist’s Guide book series—The Pragmatist's Guide to Life, The Pragmatist's Guide to Sexuality, The Pragmatist's Guide to Sexuality, and [up for publication this year] The Pragmatist's Guide to Governance and The Pragmatist's Guide to Crafting Culture).
Young scholars escaping the brain washing of the existing system (think the famous screen smashing Apple 1984 ad).
Please:
Prioritize timelessness over trendiness
Prioritize prestige over innovation
We love our existing logo, but it is borrowed from one of our books (which might be OK, but the book is on sexuality). The simple symbolism of burning down the industrial education system is powerful and obvious. We like the idea of something that is both simple and tells a compelling story.
